  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with complex legal frameworks across different jurisdictions. Here's an overview of key legal aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Counter-Terrorism and Proceeds of Crime Act\n\n3. Essential Legal Elements\n- Criminalization of money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement robust AML programs\n- Reporting large cash transactions\n- Identifying and verifying customer identities\n- Maintaining transaction records\n- Conducting regular risk assessments\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe specific implementation varies by jurisdiction, but these principles form the core of global anti-money laundering legal frameworks.",
